The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence methods to solve continuous-control tasks, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also proposes a benchmark framework for collaborative research, which involves machine learning algorithms, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics). The proposed framework can be used to evaluate and compare algorithms in physical environments, which can be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents an actual implementation of the classical mountain-car example, which involves image processing, making it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
